  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Project Manager / Site Coordinator (Interior Fit-Out)",
  "description": "<p>We are a bespoke interior fit-out and project delivery firm working across commercial, workplace, and specialist interior projects. We are seeking an experienced <strong>Project Manager / Site Coordinator</strong> who is hands-on, organised, and comfortable operating between site execution and project management.</p><p>This role suits someone who enjoys being close to the works, coordinating multiple trades, and taking ownership of day-to-day delivery while working closely with consultants, subcontractors, and clients.</p><h3><strong>The Role</strong></h3><p>You will be responsible for managing projects from site mobilisation through to handover, with key responsibilities including:</p><ul><li><p>Day-to-day site coordination and supervision of works</p></li><li><p>Managing subcontractors, sequencing, and site logistics</p></li><li><p>Programme tracking and coordination to meet key milestones</p></li><li><p>Quality control, site inspections, and defect management</p></li><li><p>Coordination of shop drawings, approvals, and RFIs</p></li><li><p>Liaison with consultants, vendors, landlords, and clients</p></li><li><p>Managing safety, access, and site compliance requirements</p></li><li><p>Supporting commercial matters such as variations and progress claims</p></li></ul><p>This is a <strong>delivery-focused role</strong> with real accountability, not a desk-only PM position.</p><h3><strong>About You</strong></h3><p>We’re looking for someone who is:</p><ul><li><p>Experienced in interior fit-out, renovation, or construction delivery</p></li><li><p>Comfortable managing both site coordination and project management responsibilities</p></li><li><p>Practical, solution-oriented, and confident on site</p></li><li><p>Strong in coordination, communication, and stakeholder management</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently and manage multiple moving parts</p></li><li><p>Familiar with subcontractor management and site sequencing</p></li></ul><p>Experience delivering commercial office or interior fit-out projects in Singapore is highly preferred.</p><h3><strong>Why Join Sorento Group</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Work on bespoke, design-led interior projects</p></li><li><p>Hands-on role with real influence over project outcomes</p></li><li><p>Direct access to senior leadership and decision-making</p></li><li><p>Lean team environment with minimal bureaucracy</p></li><li><p>Flexible working arrangements between site and office</p></li><li><p>Opportunity to grow with a fast-moving interior fit-out business</p></li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
